-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Dec 31, 2014 06:02AM EST
-- None



Dec 31 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1100 GMT on Wednesday:

**  Chinese conglomerate Fosun International Ltd <0656.HK> is making its first foray into the U.S. insurance market and buying property and casualty insurer Meadowbrook <MIG.N>, a deal that it said would help it secure funds for further acquisitions. [ID:nL3N0UE3O5]  ** Saudi Arabia's Takween Advanced Industries <1201.SE> said on Wednesday it had agreed to buy a packaging unit of the region's largest food firm Savola Group <2050.SE> for 910 million riyals ($242 million). [ID:nL6N0UF07V]  ** Polish rail freight firm PKP Cargo said on Wednesday it bought an 80-percent stake in central and eastern European competitor Advanced World Transport B.V. for 103.2 million euros ($125 million) from Czech billionaire Zdenek Bakala. [ID:nW8N0TA02A]  ** Emerging markets private equity firm Abraaj Group will pull out of the bidding process for the acquisition of Egypt's Bisco Misr <BISM.CA>, Abraaj said on Wednesday. The company had been involved in a bidding war with Kellogg Co <K.N>, the world's largest breakfast cereal maker, for the purchase of as much as 100 percent of the Egyptian snack maker. [ID:nL6N0UF08T]  ** Bank Muscat <BMAO.OM>, Oman's largest lender, has sold its brokerage business to Gulf Baader Capital Markets, a brokerage firm based in the sultanate, the lender said. [ID:nL6N0UF0BU]  ** Ballast Nedam <BALNc.AS>, a small cap Dutch builder, has been approached by Dutch and international parties about a merger or acquisition, the company said on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0UF0FM]